# Root build-context ignore — the universally-respected one (BuildKit AND the classic
# builder). It backstops the co-located docker/Dockerfile*.dockerignore files so BOTH the
# gateway (docker/Dockerfile) and the appliance (docker/Dockerfile.appliance) build from a
# LEAN context: the build copies the repo with `COPY . .` (context = repo root), so anything
# left here gets baked into the world-readable /app layer.
#
# SECURITY: without this, `COPY . .` bakes `.git`, host `node_modules`, dev `.env` files, and
# local `.plexus` gateway state (connection-key / signing secret / mesh identity) into the
# image. Keep this list ⊇ the secrets + bulk + local-state set.
#
# Paths are relative to the build context = repo root. Do NOT exclude `packages/` (the source
# the build installs + runs) or `docker/` (Dockerfiles live there). Both builds run
# `bun install` fresh on Linux, so excluding node_modules is REQUIRED, not just lean.

# ── Dependencies + build/test output (force a fresh Linux install) ──────────────────
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
**/dist
coverage
**/coverage
.bun
bun.lockb

# ── Secrets + local runtime state (MUST NOT be baked into the image) ────────────────
.env
**/.env
*.pem
**/*.pem
*.key
**/*.key
.plexus
**/.plexus

# ── VCS + logs + OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
**/*.log
.DS_Store

# ── Agent / editor / session scratch (never product) ────────────────────────────────
.pneuma
.claude/cc-master
.claude/worktrees
*.swp
scratchpad
tmp

# ── Python demo artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
.venv
.pytest_cache
examples/pomodoro-demo/agent_workdir

# ── Demo runtime artifacts (generated by run scripts, never baked in) ────────────────
docker/certs
docker/*.env
docker/.env
# The appliance's example exposed-data is operator-supplied at run time via a mount.
examples/appliance/exposed-data
